'''Hadi Sarieddine''' (born '''Hadi Saade Sarieddine''' on 4 June 1987) is a Lebanese musician best known for his work in the band [[Benevolent (band)|Benevolent]], of which he is a co-founder.

==Biography==
Hadi began to play guitar at the age of 16, after being introduced to [[Linkin Park|Linkin Park's]] [[Hybrid Theory (album)|Hybrid Theory]] and [[Metallica|Metallica's]] [[Metallica (album)|The Black Album]] by a high school friend.

Hadi joined several local bands in [[Kuwait]], discovering bands such as [[Dream Theater]], [[Symphony X]], [[Meshuggah]], & [[Opeth]] who have been cited by Hadi as his main influences as a guitar player and songwriter in several interviews.<ref>[http://jorzine.com/default.aspx?page=int&url=http://www.jorzine.com/Interviews/Interview_with_Benevolent.html JorZine.com :: Interview with Kuwait-based Lebanese metal band BENEVOLENT</title<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

In 2007, Hadi formed the band [[Benevolent (band)|Benevolent]] with brother Fadi on vocals. The band started under the name Eminence and featured a completely different sound in the early days. (More of a mellow doom style)

On November 5, 2010, [[Benevolent (band)|Benevolent]] released their debut EP titled [[Divided EP (album)|Divided]]. The album received rave reviews from critics across the globe and put the band on the map as one of the main figures in the Middle East metal scene.<ref>[http://jorzine.com/default.aspx?Page=Jorzinereviews&ID=144&year=2010 Benevolent - Divided EP :: JorZine Reviews<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

